DSC2.AS.summary: Dutch Star Companies TWO B.V., a special purpose acquisition vehicle, intends to acquire a minority stake in a business with principal business operations primarily in the Netherlands. The company was incorporated in 2020 and is based in Amsterdam, the Netherlands.

EBACU.summary: European Biotech Acquisition Corp. focuses on effecting a merger, capital stock exchange, asset acquisition, stock purchase, reorganization, or similar business combination with one or more businesses. The company was founded in 2021 and is based in Amsterdam, the Netherlands.

EFIC1.AS.summary: European FinTech IPO Company 1 B.V. is a blank check company which intends to effect a merger, capital stock exchange, asset acquisition, stock purchase, reorganization, or related business combination with businesses or entities. It focuses on the financial services and financial services technology sectors. The company was incorporated in 2021 and is based in Amsterdam, the Netherlands.

ESG.AS.summary: ESG Core Investments B.V., a special purpose acquisition company, intends to effect a merger, share exchange, share purchase, contribution in kind, asset acquisition, or related business combination to acquire majority stake in a business. The company was incorporated in 2021 and is based in Enschede, the Netherlands.

LVIDE.AS.summary: Lavide Holding N.V. does not have significant operations. Previously, it was engaged in the provision of integrated information technology solutions for medium to large-sized companies and organizations. The company was formerly known as Qurius N.V. and changed its name to Lavide Holding N.V. in July 2013. Lavide Holding N.V. was incorporated in 1998 and is based in Alkmaar, the Netherlands.

PACEU.AS.summary: Pegasus Acquisition Company Europe B.V. focuses on identifying and completing a business combination in a sub-sector of the European financial services sector. The company is based in Amsterdam, the Netherlands.
